        TextElement: Hadoop InputFormat allowing map/reduce against Cassandra rows within one ColumnFamily. [54770,54856]
        TextElement: At minimum, you need to set the CF and predicate (description of columns to extract from each row) [54865,54963]

        TextElement: simple: [55055,55062]

        TextElement: ConfigHelper.setInputSlicePredicate [55109,55144]

        TextElement: ConfigHelper.setInputSplitSize [55221,55251]
        TextElement: This should be "as big as possible, but no bigger."  Each InputSplit is read from Cassandra [55256,55347]
        TextElement: with multiple get_slice_range queries, and the per-call overhead of get_slice_range is high, [55352,55444]
        TextElement: so larger split sizes are better -- but if it is too large, you will run out of memory. [55449,55536]
        TextElement: The default split size is 64k rows. [55545,55580]
